body:
[Jsoup](http://jsoup.org/) could be a better way to parse the xml feeds

Example:

``` java
Document stations = Jsoup.connect("http://www.vlille.fr/stations/xml-stations.aspx").parser(Parser.xmlParser()).get();
Elements markers = stations.select("marker");
Element firstMarker = markers.get(0);
System.out.println(firstMarker.attr("id"));
System.out.println(firstMarker.attr("lat"));
System.out.println(firstMarker.attr("lng"));
System.out.println(firstMarker.attr("name"));

Document born = Jsoup.connect("http://www.vlille.fr/stations/xml-station.aspx?borne=1").parser(Parser.xmlParser()).get();
System.out.println(born.select("adress").text());
System.out.println(born.select("status").text());
System.out.println(born.select("bikes").text());
System.out.println(born.select("attachs").text());
System.out.println(born.select("paiement").text());
System.out.println(born.select("lastupd").text());
```

It will remove a lot of ugly code using SaxParser.
